    "description": "esm-spec §9.6.4 rule 4 (RFC out-of-line-expression-templates §7.3, §9.2): the pinned pattern-opacity divergence. A high-priority compound rule matches D(*(U,Q)); the use site factors *(U,Q) into the target-free template `flux_prod` and references it. The rewrite engine treats the surviving reference as a LEAF, so the compound pattern MUST NOT match across the reference boundary. No other rule fires, so the spatial D survives lowering (rejected only at build by the unlowered_operator gate).",
